						<summary>

						<p>This inscription records a gift of twenty <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold by Chōḻasikhāmaṇi Pallavaraiyaṉ of Nelvēli in Iṅga-nāḍu a subdivision of Chōla-nāḍu for burning a perpetual lamp. The members of the tank committee (<hi rend="italic">ērivāriyapperumakkaḷ</hi>) agreed to provide oil for burning the lamp.</p>						

